---
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How Between Sessions uses optional analytics and respects tracking choices."
>
  <header class="page-intro narrow">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy' }]} />
    <p class="eyebrow">A small, optional measurement</p>
    <h1>Privacy</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This site works without analytics. Page-view measurement begins only after you accept
      it.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="prose narrow privacy-content">
    <h2>What is measured</h2>
    <p>
      If you accept analytics, this site uses Google Analytics to count page views and
      understand which pages are visited. It does not configure advertising, ad
      personalization, custom events, user IDs, forms, or comments.
    </p>
    <p>
      Google Analytics may process information such as the page visited, approximate
      location, browser and device details, and first-party identifiers used to distinguish
      visits. Do not include personal information in URLs when linking to this site.
    </p>

    <h2>Your choice</h2>
    <p>
      Before you choose, no Google Analytics script is loaded and no analytics request is
      sent. Your choice is saved in your browser’s local storage so the site can remember
      it. Declining has no effect on the site’s content or features.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can use <strong>Tracking choices</strong> in the footer at any time. Withdrawing consent
      stops future analytics collection from this browser and removes accessible Google Analytics
      cookies set for this site.
    </p>

    <h2>Google’s processing</h2>
    <p>
      Google provides the analytics service and processes analytics information under its
      own terms and privacy practices. Learn
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites">
        how Google uses information from sites or apps that use its services</a
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
